WHERE CAN I GET PCogX-alpha^2:
------------------------------

 - Download the system:

   http://www.cs.bham.ac.uk/~grettonc/pcogx.tar.gz

 - Email Charles Gretton and ask him to send you a copy.


ON WHAT SYSTEMS HAS PCogX-alpha^2 BEEN TESTED?
---------------------------------------------------------------

	Should work on a system using the Linux 2.6.18 Kernel or
	later. Seems to work on recent version of CentOS and Ubuntu.

WHAT COMPILER IS REQUIRED?
--------------------------

We use a bunch of C++-0X features, hence a recent compiler is
required. E.g.

	gcc version 4.4.0


What's all the "CAST" stuff?
----------------------------

Good question! Needless to say never the less needless to say, it is
awesome goodness of the awesomely good variety. When I know, I will
let you know...

